cadHardwareMeasMib.name: cadHardwareMeasMib

revisions.description: Deprecate cadSFIDMeasEntry and add the following MIB objects to cadantUFIDMeasEntry cadantUFIDMeasCcfStatsSgmtValids, cadantUFIDMeasCcfStatsSgmtLost and cadantUFIDMeasCcfStatsSgmtDrop.
Add cadantUFIDMeasSIDMacIfIndex and cadantUFIDMeasSIDBonded to cadantUFIDMeasEntry
Change indices of cadDFIDMeasEntry as ifIndex and SFID. Change indices of cadantUFIDMeasEntry as ifIndex and SID
Restructure cadantHWUFIDMeasEntry, rename cadantUFIDMeasUFID to cadantUFIDMeasSID, and Add cadantHWMeasUFIDIndex
Use ifindex as key for sfid to sid lookup.
Remove fabric tables and add CPWRED tables to match implementation.
Added implementation per utilization interval for cadInterfaceUtilizationAvgContSlots.
Added cadDFIDMeasPolicedDelayPkts for Traffic Shaping feature.
Extended cadSubMgtPktFilterExtTable to allow for packet capturing.
Added support for per-SID HCS and CRC errors.
Added support for per UFID microreflection/signalnoise.
Added 10 BCM3214 counts to the cadantUPortMeasTable
add more receive error counts to cadantEtherPhyMeasTable
add error drop and filter drop counts to UPortMeas table
Add support for DHCP packets dropped due to throttling.

cadHardwareMeasMib.description: This Mib Module contains all of the counts that are associated with hardware in the ARRIS C4 CMTS. Many of these MIB variables contain the same counts as found in the standard MIBs. However, the grouping of these variables is done for the convenience of the Cadant engineering team. These tables can be used to build value-added interfaces to the Cadant ARRIS C4 CMTS.

PktClassId.name: PktClassId
PktClassId.description: Index assigned to packet classifier entry by the CMTS which is unique per service flow.

SIDValue.name: SIDValue
SIDValue.description: The 1's-based SID. 0 is used when there is no SID, such as for downstream flows.

TMSide.name: TMSide
TMSide.description: The Traffic Manager side no SID, such as for downstream flows.

cadantFabActualDepth.name: cadantFabActualDepth
cadantFabActualDepth.description: The current depth of the fabric.

cadantFabAvgDepth.name: cadantFabAvgDepth
cadantFabAvgDepth.description: The average depth of the fabric.

cadantUPortMeasTable.name: cadantUPortMeasTable
cadantUPortMeasTable.description: This table contains information relevant to D Card upstream channels.

cadantUPortMeasUcastFrms.name: cadantUPortMeasUcastFrms
cadantUPortMeasUcastFrms.description: The aggregrate number of unicast frames received on this U channel, whether dropped or passed. This includes MAC packets.

cadantUPortMeasMcastFrms.name: cadantUPortMeasMcastFrms
cadantUPortMeasMcastFrms.description: The aggregrate number of multicast frames received on this U channel, whether dropped or passed. This includes MAC packets.

cadantUPortMeasBcastFrms.name: cadantUPortMeasBcastFrms
cadantUPortMeasBcastFrms.description: The aggregrate number of broadcast frames received on this U channel, whether dropped or passed. This includes MAC packets.

cadantUPortMeasUcastDataFrms.name: cadantUPortMeasUcastDataFrms
cadantUPortMeasUcastDataFrms.description: The aggregrate number of unicast frames received on this U channel, whether dropped or passed. This does not include MAC packets.

cadantUPortMeasMcastDataFrms.name: cadantUPortMeasMcastDataFrms
cadantUPortMeasMcastDataFrms.description: The aggregrate number of multicast frames received on this U channel, whether dropped or passed. This does not include MAC packets.

cadantUPortMeasBcastDataFrms.name: cadantUPortMeasBcastDataFrms
cadantUPortMeasBcastDataFrms.description: The aggregrate number of broadcast frames received on this U channel, whether dropped or passed. This does not include MAC packets.

cadantUPortMeasDiscardFrms.name: cadantUPortMeasDiscardFrms
cadantUPortMeasDiscardFrms.description: The aggregrate number of frames received on this U channel that were dropped for reasons other than ErrorFrms or FilterFrms.

cadantUPortMeasIfInOctets.name: cadantUPortMeasIfInOctets
cadantUPortMeasIfInOctets.description: The aggregrate number of octets received on this U channel. This includes MAC packets and the length of the MAC header.

cadantUPortMeasIfInDataOctets.name: cadantUPortMeasIfInDataOctets
cadantUPortMeasIfInDataOctets.description: The aggregrate number of octets received on this U channel. This does not include MAC packets or the length of the MAC header.

cadantUPortMeasIfInUnknownProtos.name: cadantUPortMeasIfInUnknownProtos
cadantUPortMeasIfInUnknownProtos.description: Aggregrate number of MAC frames with unknown protocol. This count is neither mutually exclusive with cadantUPortMeasErroredFrms nor cadantUPortMeasErroredFrms.

cadantUPortMeasAppMinusBWReqFrms.name: cadantUPortMeasAppMinusBWReqFrms
cadantUPortMeasAppMinusBWReqFrms.description: The number of (unicast) frames received by the software application which are not bandwidth request frames.

cadantUPortMeasErroredFrms.name: cadantUPortMeasErroredFrms
cadantUPortMeasErroredFrms.description: The aggregrate number of packets received on this U channel that were received in error and dropped. This count is neither mutually exclusive with cadantUPortMeasIfInUnknownProtos nor cadantUPortMeasFilteredFrms.

cadantUPortMeasFilteredFrms.name: cadantUPortMeasFilteredFrms
cadantUPortMeasFilteredFrms.description: The aggregrate number of packets received on this U channel that were dropped due to a filter rule match and discard. This count is neither mutually exclusive with cadantUPortMeasIfInUnknownProtos nor cadantUPortMeasErroredFrms.

cadantUPortMeasBcastReqColls.name: cadantUPortMeasBcastReqColls
cadantUPortMeasBcastReqColls.description: Broadcast contention request opportunities with possible collisions count

cadantUPortMeasBcastReqNoEnergies.name: cadantUPortMeasBcastReqNoEnergies
cadantUPortMeasBcastReqNoEnergies.description: Broadcast contention request opportunities with no energy condition detected

cadantUPortMeasBcastReqRxPwr1s.name: cadantUPortMeasBcastReqRxPwr1s
cadantUPortMeasBcastReqRxPwr1s.description: Broadcast contention request opportunities with received power level between power threshold 2 and power threshold 1

cadantUPortMeasBcastReqRxPwr2s.name: cadantUPortMeasBcastReqRxPwr2s
cadantUPortMeasBcastReqRxPwr2s.description: Broadcast contention request opportunities with received power level greater than power threshold 2

cadantUPortMeasInitMaintColls.name: cadantUPortMeasInitMaintColls
cadantUPortMeasInitMaintColls.description: Initial maintenance opportunities with possible collision

cadantUPortMeasInitMaintNoEnergies.name: cadantUPortMeasInitMaintNoEnergies
cadantUPortMeasInitMaintNoEnergies.description: Initial maintenance opportunities with no energy detected

cadantUPortMeasInitMaintRxPwr1s.name: cadantUPortMeasInitMaintRxPwr1s
cadantUPortMeasInitMaintRxPwr1s.description: Initial maintenance opportunities with received power level between power threshold 2 and power threshold 1

cadantUPortMeasInitMaintRxPwr2s.name: cadantUPortMeasInitMaintRxPwr2s
cadantUPortMeasInitMaintRxPwr2s.description: Initial maintenance opportunities with received power level greater than power threshold 2

cadantDPortMeasIfOutUcastPkts.name: cadantDPortMeasIfOutUcastPkts
cadantDPortMeasIfOutUcastPkts.description: Aggregrate number of unicast data packets sent on this D channel. This includes MAC mgmt messages.

cadantDPortMeasIfOutMcastPkts.name: cadantDPortMeasIfOutMcastPkts
cadantDPortMeasIfOutMcastPkts.description: Aggregrate number of multicast data packets sent on this D channel. This includes MAC mgmt messages.

cadantDPortMeasIfOutBcastPkts.name: cadantDPortMeasIfOutBcastPkts
cadantDPortMeasIfOutBcastPkts.description: Aggregrate number of broadcast data packets sent on this D channel. This includes MAC mgmt messages.

cadantDPortMeasIfOutDataOctets.name: cadantDPortMeasIfOutDataOctets
cadantDPortMeasIfOutDataOctets.description: Aggregrate number of data bytes sent on this D channel. This does not include MAC mgmt bytes.

cadantDPortMeasIfOutUcastDataPkts.name: cadantDPortMeasIfOutUcastDataPkts
cadantDPortMeasIfOutUcastDataPkts.description: Aggregrate number of unicast data packets sent on this D channel. This does not include MAC mgmt messages.

cadantDPortMeasIfOutMcastDataPkts.name: cadantDPortMeasIfOutMcastDataPkts
cadantDPortMeasIfOutMcastDataPkts.description: Aggregrate number of multicast data packets sent on this D channel. This does not include MAC mgmt messages.

cadantDPortMeasIfOutBcastDataPkts.name: cadantDPortMeasIfOutBcastDataPkts
cadantDPortMeasIfOutBcastDataPkts.description: Aggregrate number of broadcast data packets sent on this D channel. This does not include MAC mgmt messages.

cadantDPortMeasSyncPkts.name: cadantDPortMeasSyncPkts
cadantDPortMeasSyncPkts.description: Aggregrate number of sync. frames sent on this D channel.

cadantDPortMeasAppUcastPkts.name: cadantDPortMeasAppUcastPkts
cadantDPortMeasAppUcastPkts.description: Aggregrate number of unicast DOCSIS Mac mgmt messages sent by application software.

cadantDPortMeasAppMcastPkts.name: cadantDPortMeasAppMcastPkts
cadantDPortMeasAppMcastPkts.description: Aggregrate number of multicast DOCSIS Mac mgmt messages sent by application software.

cadantDPortMeasIfOutTotalOctets.name: cadantDPortMeasIfOutTotalOctets
cadantDPortMeasIfOutTotalOctets.description: Aggregrate number of octets sent by application software.

cadantDPortMeasOfdmHighestAvgBitsPerSubc.name: cadantDPortMeasOfdmHighestAvgBitsPerSubc
cadantDPortMeasOfdmHighestAvgBitsPerSubc.description: Highest average bits per subcarrier among all the data profiles of the downstream OFDM channel.

cadantDPortMeasOfdmNumDataSubc.name: cadantDPortMeasOfdmNumDataSubc
cadantDPortMeasOfdmNumDataSubc.description: The number of data subcarrier of the downstream OFDM channel.

cadantDPortMeasOfdmChanUtilization.name: cadantDPortMeasOfdmChanUtilization
cadantDPortMeasOfdmChanUtilization.description: The utilization of the downstream OFDM channel.

cadantUFIDMeasPktsSGreedyDrop.name: cadantUFIDMeasPktsSGreedyDrop
cadantUFIDMeasPktsSGreedyDrop.description: The aggregrate number of Super Greedy pkts dropped for this UFID for this MAC layer.

cadantUFIDMeasBytsOtherDrop.name: cadantUFIDMeasBytsOtherDrop
cadantUFIDMeasBytsOtherDrop.description: The aggregrate number of bytes dropped for this UFID for this MAC layer for any other reason than Super Greedy.

cadantUFIDMeasBytsArrived.name: cadantUFIDMeasBytsArrived
cadantUFIDMeasBytsArrived.description: The aggregrate number of bytes that arrived for this UFID for this MAC layer.

cadantUFIDMeasPktsArrived.name: cadantUFIDMeasPktsArrived
cadantUFIDMeasPktsArrived.description: The aggregrate number of packets that arrived for this UFID for this MAC layer.

cadantUFIDMeasSIDCorrecteds.name: cadantUFIDMeasSIDCorrecteds
cadantUFIDMeasSIDCorrecteds.description: The aggregrate number of bytes that had errors and were corrected for this UFID for this MAC layer.

cadantUFIDMeasSIDUnerroreds.name: cadantUFIDMeasSIDUnerroreds
cadantUFIDMeasSIDUnerroreds.description: The aggregrate number of bytes that had no errors for this UFID for this MAC layer.

cadantUFIDMeasSIDUnCorrecteds.name: cadantUFIDMeasSIDUnCorrecteds
cadantUFIDMeasSIDUnCorrecteds.description: The aggregrate number of bytes that had errors and were not corrected for this UFID for this MAC layer.

cadantUFIDMeasSIDNoUniqueWordDetecteds.name: cadantUFIDMeasSIDNoUniqueWordDetecteds
cadantUFIDMeasSIDNoUniqueWordDetecteds.description: The aggregrate number of bytes allocated for this UFID in which no unique code word was detected for this UFID for this MAC layer.

cadantUFIDMeasSIDCollidedBursts.name: cadantUFIDMeasSIDCollidedBursts

cadantUFIDMeasSIDNoEnergyDetecteds.name: cadantUFIDMeasSIDNoEnergyDetecteds

cadantUFIDMeasSIDLengthErrors.name: cadantUFIDMeasSIDLengthErrors

cadantUFIDMeasSIDMACErrors.name: cadantUFIDMeasSIDMACErrors

cadantUFIDMeasSCN.name: cadantUFIDMeasSCN

cadantUFIDMeasSFID.name: cadantUFIDMeasSFID
cadantUFIDMeasSFID.description: The SFID this UFID(SID) is for.

cadantUFIDMeasSIDHCSErrors.name: cadantUFIDMeasSIDHCSErrors
cadantUFIDMeasSIDHCSErrors.description: The number of MAC HCS errors seen for this SID.

cadantUFIDMeasSIDCRCErrors.name: cadantUFIDMeasSIDCRCErrors
cadantUFIDMeasSIDCRCErrors.description: The number of MAC CRC errors seen for this SID.

cadantUFIDMeasGateID.name: cadantUFIDMeasGateID
cadantUFIDMeasGateID.description: The DQoS or PCMM gate ID corresponding to the flow, A zero in this field indicates no gate is associated with the flow.

cadantUFIDMeasSIDMacIfIndex.name: cadantUFIDMeasSIDMacIfIndex

cadantUFIDMeasSIDBonded.name: cadantUFIDMeasSIDBonded
cadantUFIDMeasSIDBonded.description: This object indicates whether a SID is associated with a CCF service flow.

cadantUFIDMeasCcfStatsSgmtValids.name: cadantUFIDMeasCcfStatsSgmtValids
cadantUFIDMeasCcfStatsSgmtValids.description: This attribute contains the number of segments counted on this service flow regardless of whether the fragment was correctly reassembled into valid packets. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system.

cadantUFIDMeasCcfStatsSgmtLost.name: cadantUFIDMeasCcfStatsSgmtLost
cadantUFIDMeasCcfStatsSgmtLost.description: This attribute counts the number of segments which the CMTS segment reassembly function determines were lost. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system.

cadantUFIDMeasCcfStatsSgmtDrop.name: cadantUFIDMeasCcfStatsSgmtDrop
cadantUFIDMeasCcfStatsSgmtDrop.description: This attribute counts the number of segments which the CMTS segment reassembly function determines were dropped. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system.

cadDFIDMeasIndex.name: cadDFIDMeasIndex
cadDFIDMeasIndex.description: The SFID these DFID counts are for.

cadDFIDMeasBytsArrived.name: cadDFIDMeasBytsArrived
cadDFIDMeasBytsArrived.description: The aggregrate number of bytes arriving to go out, but not necessarily transmitted.

cadDFIDMeasPktsArrived.name: cadDFIDMeasPktsArrived
cadDFIDMeasPktsArrived.description: The aggregrate number of packets arriving to go out, but not necessarily transmitted.

cadDFIDMeasBytsDropped.name: cadDFIDMeasBytsDropped
cadDFIDMeasBytsDropped.description: The aggregrate number of bytes dropped.

cadDFIDMeasPktsDropped.name: cadDFIDMeasPktsDropped
cadDFIDMeasPktsDropped.description: The aggregrate number of packets dropped.

cadDFIDMeasBytsUnkDropped.name: cadDFIDMeasBytsUnkDropped
cadDFIDMeasBytsUnkDropped.description: The aggregrate number of bytes dropped due to unknown DMAC.

cadDFIDMeasMacAddress.name: cadDFIDMeasMacAddress
cadDFIDMeasMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the CM this flow is associated with.

cadDFIDMeasSCN.name: cadDFIDMeasSCN
cadDFIDMeasSCN.description: The Service Class Name for this flow.

cadDFIDMeasGateID.name: cadDFIDMeasGateID
cadDFIDMeasGateID.description: The DQoS or PCMM gate ID corresponding to the flow, A zero in this field indicates no gate is associated with the flow.

cadQosPktClassMeasTable.name: cadQosPktClassMeasTable

cadQosPktClassMeasSFID.name: cadQosPktClassMeasSFID

cadQosPktClassMeasPkts.name: cadQosPktClassMeasPkts
cadQosPktClassMeasPkts.description: The number of packets that have been classified using this classifier on this flow.

Every row that appears in this table should have a corresponding row in both the ifTable and the ifXTable. However, not every row in the ifTable and ifXTable will appear in this table.

cadInterfaceUtilizationTable.name: cadInterfaceUtilizationTable
cadInterfaceUtilizationTable.description: Reports utilization statistics for attached interfaces.

cadInterfaceUtilizationEntry.name: cadInterfaceUtilizationEntry
cadInterfaceUtilizationEntry.description: Utilization statistics for a single interface. An entry exists in this table for each ifEntry with an ifType equal to docsCableDownstreamInterface (128), docsCableUpstreamInterface (129), docsCableUpstreamChannel (205), ethernet(6), or gigabitEthernet(117).

cadInterfaceUtilizationDirection.name: cadInterfaceUtilizationDirection
cadInterfaceUtilizationDirection.description: The direction of flow this utilization is for. Cable upstream interfaces will only have a value of 'in' for this object. Likewise, cable downstream interfaces will only hav a value of 'out' for this object. Full-duplex interfaces, such as fastEthernet and gigabitEthernet interfaces, will have both 'in' and 'out' rows.

cadInterfaceUtilizationPercentage.name: cadInterfaceUtilizationPercentage
cadInterfaceUtilizationPercentage.description: The calculated and truncated utilization index for this interface, accurate as of the most recent docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationInterval.

cadInterfaceUtilizationAvgContSlots.name: cadInterfaceUtilizationAvgContSlots
cadInterfaceUtilizationAvgContSlots.description: Applicable for ifType of docsCableUpstreamChannel (205) only. The average percentage of contention mini-slots for upstream channel. This ratio is calculated the most recent utilization interval. Formula: Upstream contention mini-slots utilization = (100 * ((contention mini-slots ) / (total mini-slots))

cadInterfaceHighResUtilizationPercentage.name: cadInterfaceHighResUtilizationPercentage
cadInterfaceHighResUtilizationPercentage.description: The calculated and truncated utilization index for this interface, accurate (to 0.01% resolution) as of the most recent docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationInterval.

cadInterfaceIntervalOctetsForwarded.name: cadInterfaceIntervalOctetsForwarded
cadInterfaceIntervalOctetsForwarded.description: The number of octets forwarded since the most recent docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationInterval. Note that this count will only apply to the following interface types: Ethernet, Link-Aggregate. For all other interface types this value will display 0

cadSubMgtPktFilterExtTable.name: cadSubMgtPktFilterExtTable
cadSubMgtPktFilterExtTable.description: This table augments the docsSubMgtPktFilterTable. In its current form, it is used to clear docsSubMgtPktFilterMatches and keep track of the change.

cadSubMgtPktFilterExtEntry.name: cadSubMgtPktFilterExtEntry
cadSubMgtPktFilterExtEntry.description: For every docsSubmgt3FilterGrpEntry, there is a matching cadSubMgtPktFilterExtEntry.

cadSubMgtPktFilterMatchesReset.name: cadSubMgtPktFilterMatchesReset
cadSubMgtPktFilterMatchesReset.description: This object always return false(2) when read. If the value false(2) is assigned to this object, no action is taken. However, if this object it set to the value true(1), the corresponding docsSubMgtPktFilterMatches counter object is set to 0 and cadSubMgtPktFilterLastChanged is set to the current time.

cadSubMgtPktFilterLastChanged.name: cadSubMgtPktFilterLastChanged
cadSubMgtPktFilterLastChanged.description: The time at which docsSubMgtPktFilterMatches might have experienced a discontinuity, such as when cadSubMgtPktFilterMatchesReset is set to true(1) or when any of the parameters in the docsSubMgtPktFilterTable affecting filtering last changed.

cadSubMgtPktFilterCaptureEnabled.name: cadSubMgtPktFilterCaptureEnabled
cadSubMgtPktFilterCaptureEnabled.description: Indicates whether packets matching this filter are captured for possible debug logging. A value of true indicates that packets matching this filter will be captured. A value of false indicates that packets matching this filter will not be captured for later debuggging.

cadLaesCountEntry.name: cadLaesCountEntry
cadLaesCountEntry.description: For every cadLaesCountEntry, there is a matching pktcEScTapStreamEntry.

cadLaesCountMacDomainIfIndex.name: cadLaesCountMacDomainIfIndex
cadLaesCountMacDomainIfIndex.description: This object indicates the cable Mac domain interface index that the LAES stream is associated with.

cadLaesCountStreamDirection.name: cadLaesCountStreamDirection
cadLaesCountStreamDirection.description: This object indicates either downstream or upstream direction that the LAES stream is associated with.

cadLaesCountInterceptedPackets.name: cadLaesCountInterceptedPackets
cadLaesCountInterceptedPackets.description: Indicates number of intercepted packets are sent of the LAES stream.

cadLaesCountInterceptDrops.name: cadLaesCountInterceptDrops
cadLaesCountInterceptDrops.description: Indicates number of intercepted packets are dropped of the LAES stream.

cadFftUpstreamChannelEntry.name: cadFftUpstreamChannelEntry
cadFftUpstreamChannelEntry.description: FFT status for a single upstream channel with ifType docsCableUpstreamInterface(129).

cadFftInProgress.name: cadFftInProgress
cadFftInProgress.description: The current state on the FFT capture.

cadFftCurrentTriggers.name: cadFftCurrentTriggers
cadFftCurrentTriggers.description: The number of times the FFT capture has triggered and transferred data from the Broadcom device.
